			<p>A string is wrapped many times around a tennis ball that has mass <m>m = 60 \mathrm{~g}</m> and radius <m>r = 7 \mathrm{~cm}</m>.  For a hollow ball, <m>I = \frac{2}{3}mr^2</m> about the center or <m>I = \frac{5}{3}mr^2</m> about the edge â€” calculating these for yourself is a good challenge!  The string is attached to the ceiling and the ball is allowed to fall (see the figure below). Determine the tension in the string.</p>
		</statement>
